title: For Sale:  Custom AR15 5.56
postcontent:
Selling my custom AR15.  This was my first 5.56 AR build.  I have decided to build another most expensive rifle.  This rifle was built less than a year ago and I've put close to 200 rounds through it and have not had any malfunctions or stoppages of any kind.  Rifle has no optics or sights.  Here is the parts list that I used to build the rifle. 
- Anderson Lower- Aero Precision upper- Tapco Lower Parts Kit- Anderson Bolt Carrier group- Magpul stock on a mil-spec buffer tube- BCM Gun Fighter Mod 4 charging handle- BCM 16" M4 profile barrel- BCM low profile gas block- 3 prong flash hider- No name 15" quad rail- Magpul grip- Metal vertical Grip- Sling adpater back plateThe rifle also comes with the following- Two 30 round magpul gen 2 PMAGS- One 30 round polymer Mag of another brand- Plano gunguard case- Single point sling- 70 rounds of green tip- I also have more ammo that will go with it but I do not know the exact round count.  Probably another 50 - 100.  THE BAD:
The only negative thing I can say about the gun is the coating.  I put a spray on duracoat and it just didn't go well.  It had rubbed off in some areas and there are runs on other parts.  That being said if you plan on having it coated or just don't care what your gun looks like then it's not an issue.  Either way I'm going to set the price low. 
 
I know the coating and the fact this is a custom rifle can turn people off so I will let it all go for $600.  Will not split up.  I fired 90 rounds through this rifle just today including a mag dump.  The rifle shoots flawlessly.
